# docstring

Extracts docstrings from Python modules.

## Key insight

Docstrings tell agents WHAT functions/classes do - descriptions, parameters, returns, examples.

## What docstrings typically contain

- One-line summary
- Extended description
- Parameters (name, type, description)
- Returns description
- Examples (often in doctest format)
- See also references

## Limitations

- Not all modules have good docstrings
- Format varies (Google style, NumPy style, plain)
- May be outdated vs actual code
- Private methods often lack docs

## How p1cli displays

- Shows first 30 lines by default in text mode
- Full docstring in JSON mode
- Combined with signature when both requested

## For agents

Read docstrings alongside signatures - together they provide complete picture:
- Signature = how to call
- Docstring = what it does, what parameters mean
